8  Appendix 3 
OUTLINE TERMS OF REFERENCE  

A.  Part A: Consulting Services for Preparing the Project 
1.  The consultant will provide the following outputs: 

(i)  a review of air quality issues in the project area and the rationale for and benefits 
of using compressed natural gas (CNG); 
(ii)  a study of the current status of the use of natural gas for transportation in 
developing and developed countries; 
(iii)  a  review  of  the  existing  Indonesian  policies,  regulations,  standards,  and 
guidelines for the use of natural gas for transportation and industry sectors, and 
related projects being considered by other funding agencies; 
(iv)  a study of the market and investment needs for CNG use in Greater Jakarta; 
(v)  a design of potential investment components of the proposed project, including 
but not limited to, gas filling stations, gas conversion kits, financing mechanism 
for private sectors to use clean fuels, dissemination program, etc; options for 
CNG supply (other than pipeline); projections regarding adoption of CNG; vehicle 
emission testing equipment; and a traffic air quality monitoring system; 
(vi)  a project framework, with a specific, timebound, and monitorable set of outputs 
and activities; 
(vii)  an economic and financial analysis of the proposed project; 
(viii)  an environmental impact assessment (EIA) and a summary EIA of the project; 
(ix)  a social impact and poverty study for the proposed project; 
(x)  in  all  cases  involving  land  acquisition,  guidance  and  supervision  for  the 
Perusahaan  Gas  Negara  (PGN)  staff  in  preparing  the  land acquisition and 
resettlement plan (LARP) acceptable to Asian Development Bank (ADB);  
(xi)  a study of the possibility of accessing Global Environment Facility (GEF) funds; 
and 
(xii)  a training program for PGN to promote the use of natural gas in vehicles; 

2.  To prepare the required outputs, the consultants will work as a team to carry out various 
tasks, under the supervision and coordination of the team leader and the deputy team leader. 
The tasks will include but not be limited to the following. 

1.  Strategic Plan for Promoting CNG to Improve Air Quality  
3.  The international CNG automotive specialist and team leader and domestic environment 
specialist  and  deputy  team  leader  will  carry  out  the  following  tasks,  with  the  support  of 
international natural gas sector specialist, and domestic natural gas specialist. The consultants 
will 
(i)  review reports on urban transport in Indonesia, particularly studies related to 
passenger traffic and vehicular emissions; 
(ii)  review the Government’s development policies and plans for the gas subsector 
and urban transport;   
(iii)  review reports on switching the fuel for passenger transport, and compare the 
advantages and disadvantages of using CNG; 
(iv)  provide technical justification for the proposed project, and review or carry out a 
feasibility study for each project component;
